args:
The prince wins a pact with the Flamewyrm,
and the mana in their pactstone quiets the
volcano's ire. The Flamewyrm has grown fond
of the prince and, before joining him, assumes
human form and a human name—Mym.
You possess great strength, boy—\nthe kind I've not seen in quite some time.
And let it be known I loathe saying that.\nWhat a dreadful day this is shaping into...
I can tell you enjoyed the fight.\nBut why did you hold back?
Maybe I just didn't feel like hurting you.
Answer me this: Why do you seek power?
As prince, I have a duty to protect the\npeople of my kingdom.
And I gave my sister Zethia my word that\nI would forge a pact with you.
I knew you had a motive.
Maybe, but none of that was in my mind\nwhen I came here. All I knew was that I\nhad to stop the volcano.
And I also had to make sure you were safe.
Before, when I told you we came to help,\nyou asked why you should believe me.
You were like a child that was about to cry.
And I can't abandon someone like that.
THAT was your reason? ...You are a very\nstrange man, little Prince.
Much as I'm enjoyin' all this witty banter,\nthe tremors are gettin' worse.
Maybe you could speed it up a little?
The magma has nearly reached us.\nForge the pact, before the volcano erupts!
Tsk! Such boors. Must you spoil my first\npleasant conversation in years?
Flamewyrm, will you forge a pact with me?
Together, we can do more than just stop\na single volcano. I sense it, and I know\nyou do as well.
Yes. I shall remember those words.
And if you fail me in any way whatsoever,\nI shall reduce you to ash.
By the blood that runs through me,\nlet my fire now be part of your flame.
I have been waiting for a man like you\nto appear for quite some time.
The last such man was Alberius, at whose\nside I fought in ages past.
But that was only to protect this volcano,\nthe place of my birth.
With you, I believe we can go further.\nI might even be talked out of my home!
You have proven yourself. I accept.
{player_name}, dragon defender!\nI acknowledge you as my true king!
I am Brunhilda, mistress of crimson,\nthe inferno clad, and the flame that shall\nguide your way!
Uh, the ground's still shaking...\nIt's about to erupt!
The magma has stilled as well.\nThe pact must have worked.
Each pactstone contains a vast quantity\nof mana condensed into crystal form.
Our stone absorbed all the mana that was\nout of balance.
And thank you as well, Brunhilda.\nWe owe you our lives.
Enough with the formalities.\nYou and I are one now.
I don't mind the age difference so much,\nbut the appearance difference will take\nsome getting used to...
Ta-daaah! Do I look human now?
Holy cow! The dragon lady just turned\ninto a LADY lady!
Uh...let's start with...wow?\nI didn't know dragons could shapeshift.
Not all can. I just happen to be more\nresourceful than most. You may shower\nme with praise at any time now.
I suppose if people can become dragons,\nthere's nothing to get in the way of\ndragons becoming people.
Save for all known logic and reason.\nBut I admire your ability to simply accept\nthings with such grace.
Leaving the volcano will drain some of\nmy power, but so be it.
Now all that I need is a new name.\nSomething rather short and easy,\nso humans can remember it.
Oh, and as it turns out, the woman you're\nlooking at was one of Alberius's erstwhile\ncompanions. I've...borrowed her form.
She was a great adventurer, and her\nname...was Mym!
That's what you may call me. Mym.
It's certainly short and easy to remember.
It's good to meet you, Mym.

Having made a pact with the third of the
Six Greatwyrms, Brunhilda, and having
quelled the wrath of Mount Adolla,
the prince and his companions press on.
He has dragonblood, while his sister\nis the Auspex. Each now sets out on a\npath to fulfill their respective roles.
The day will soon come when their fates again\nintertwine. Little do they realize that it will also\nbe the day of their parting.
